<subSubSection id="2988C0B9A322520C71726C9711373DFF" pageNumber="704" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1D8FD7679488AA3C8BFF45458C5A8B0D" pageNumber="704">
<emphasis id="5FAD3A3236A7E07E4982EC27605B9FFB" italics="true" pageNumber="704">Note:</emphasis>
The varietal epithet was originally spelled 
<normalizedToken id="02385678E99D231B55E7E389AF58B774" originalValue="“adrachnites”">&quot;adrachnites&quot;</normalizedToken>
in the protologue but was subsequently corrected by Linnaeus. Rothmaler (in 
<emphasis id="2B5281CAAFC4135987128587553C0D3A" italics="true" pageNumber="704">Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg.</emphasis>
49: 280. 1940) treated this as the basionym of 
<taxonomicName id="C546C8DDF87D0480E84CF3DF57B67E53" authority="(L.) L. (1754)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1754" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ophrys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arachnites">
<emphasis id="233921719AA332437B5FD6A2185BA06D" italics="true" pageNumber="704">O. arachnites</emphasis>
(L.) L. (1754)
</taxonomicName>
, followed by Greuter (in 
<emphasis id="F6DD59E33C7BCC1876132AF3692329DD" italics="true" pageNumber="704">Candollea</emphasis>
44: 566. 1989). However, Britten (in 
<emphasis id="D6F5EA8DB75C6E4EE24BA8F3872DE69C" italics="true" pageNumber="704">J. Bot.</emphasis>
47, Suppl. 1909; 50: 312-314. 1912) argued that 
<emphasis id="311C9A397997D82E15783A4B68796E62" italics="true" pageNumber="704">
&quot;
<taxonomicName id="17DA4FBE960CA26DA9833B888A86EEA9" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ophrys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arachnites">O. arachnites</taxonomicName>
&quot;
</emphasis>
resulted from a typographic error. Stearn (
<emphasis id="3F29CFE6F8DE96BF8C34FE8FB099295A" italics="true" pageNumber="704">
Introd. 
<normalizedToken id="C865D6C2E34DBEA7D9ED3F56E9C7E16D" originalValue="Ray’s">Ray's</normalizedToken>
Syn. Meth. Stirp. Brit.
</emphasis>
(Ray Soc. ed.): 42-68. 1973) evidently agreed as he did not list the name as new.
</paragraph>
